 times before tending to its on-shell limit. On the\nother hand, the unstable and acausal attractors have non-negative entropy\ndivergence. We speculate that the violation of the second law by stable and\ncausal off-shell parameters is required for stability of the first-order\nhydrodynamics. We investigate the analytical structure of the Borel-transformed\nseries and find the proper relation between the poles and nonhydro modes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Feb 2020 22:38:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Feb 2020 08:59:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 31 Mar 2020 09:00:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 19 Jun 2020 10:54:40 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 16 Aug 2020 06:46:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-02"}
